Imagine where you could be a year from now. Comment “link” for my fat loss round starting Monday!! I have a few spots left 

What if you  stopped taking short cuts and stopped the short term fixes? …If you decided to dedicated yourself to YOU for an entire year? Imagine waking up in 2026 being proud of what you accomplished and never have to make a weight loss resolution again. 

Being fit is the ultimate sign of discipline. No one can go to the gym for you, no one can eat healthy for you, no one can do the work for you. 

99% of you are not the exception to the rule. Whatever excuse you tell yourself to remove accountability from your crappy eating, lack of consistency and patience, and poor choices are only going to leave you in the same spot you are now. 

Nothing changes if nothing changes. This won’t be a new year for you if you don’t make change, it’ll just be another year. So if you’re sick of starting over, stop stopping. 

If you need the big sister energy for this year-I’m your girl! Comment link now!

The year of not “becoming” someone but the year of unbecoming everything and getting rid of everyone that no longer aligns with who we want to become. 

Share if you agree!!! 

The year of complete peace, total calmness and trusting God more than ever before. I can explain that sense of security and happiness I have starting the year, but this community will be the best it’s ever been 🫶🏻

Comment “link” to join me in my 2025 fitness journey ! I’ll be starting my next faster way round MONDAY and I would love to have you by my side. 

No-I don’t hate my body, I hate how I felt and how my clothes fit. I love myself, my growth, and my focus in a sickening diet culture world. I was gaslighting myself in thinking I had to stay the same, because it was relatable. You are allowed to grow, change and become who you want and the right people will relate! 

I gained 17 lbs in 23-24 (mostly fat lbs). Every lb gained is because of me and my actions (or lack there of). Not my hormones, my kids, my travels, my tiredness, -everything falls on my shoulders. I had a come to Jesus moment last week and finally looked myself dead in the eye and said. “You are the only one who can take control of your life”. And that’s exactly what I’m doing. 

2025 is your comeback year/let’s go 🫶🏻

#ad Need a quick and satisfying treat that keeps you on track with your fitness goals? Try this Vanilla Protein Mug Cake, ready in just minutes!  

I used my @optimumnutrition Gold Standard Whey, which I bought at Target! With 24g of high-quality protein and BCAAs, it’s the perfect quick protein powder to help support your goals this new year!   

Grab the recipe below and Gold Standard Whey and enjoy a delicious, protein-packed dessert tonight!

Recipe:
• Ingredients:
• 1 scoop Optimum Nutrition
Vanilla Protein Powder
• 2 tablespoons flour
• ¼ teaspoon baking powder
• ¼ teaspoon cinnamon
• 1 egg
• 2 tablespoons milk
• ½ teaspoon vanilla extract

Instructions:
1 In a microwave-safe mug, whisk together the dry ingredients: protein powder, flour, baking powder, and cinnamon.
2 Stir in the egg, milk, and vanilla extract until the batter is smooth and well combined.
3 Microwave on high for 60
seconds. The cake should rise and be firm to the touch but not dry.
4 Allow the mug cake to cool slightly, then top with a drizzle of maple syrup, a dollop of whipped cream, or a sprinkle of cinnamon!

What if you stopped taking short cuts and stopped the short term fixes? …If you decided to dedicated yourself to YOU for an entire year? Imagine waking up in 2026 being proud of what you accomplished and never have to make a weight loss resolution again. 

Being fit is the ultimate sign of discipline. No one can go to the gym for you, no one can eat healthy for you, no one can do the work for you. 

99% of you are not the exception to the rule. Whatever excuse you tell yourself to remove accountability from your crappy eating, lack of consistency and patience, and poor choices are only going to leave you in the same spot you are now. 

Nothing changes if nothing changes. This won’t be a new year for you if you don’t make change, it’ll just be another year. So if you’re sick of starting over, stop stopping.

It’s ok if you want to lose weight. There I said it- in fact, if it’s to BETTER your health and happiness, I encourage it.

But before you can achieve it, you have to promise yourself you’ll stay consistent. 

The promises you make to yourself are the hardest to keep and easiest to break. 

The reason you lack confidence is because you lack self belief. And the reason you lack self belief is because you dont keep the promises you make to yourself. 

Ive told myself for years i would keep weight off once and for all- yet i always found a reason to stop because no one was looking. 

8 months ago  I finally stuck with it - not because i want to share it here, but because i promised myself i would do it- and im keeping that promise. And now im down 17 lbs in 8 months 

When you make promises to yourself and you dont keep them, you reinforce the thought pattern that you are someone who doesnt follow thru-

Just starting with the little shit- making my bed, going to the gym, saving the money- follow thru on what you said you will do and it’ll bleed into every other capacity of your life

Show up. For you. But also for the people who are praying on your downfall 🫶🏻
